article_text:
Mumbai Heavy Rain Delays Local Trains Up To 20 Minutes, Flights And Road Traffic Disrupted
Curated By :
Samreen Pall
News18.com
Last Updated:
June 16, 2025, 10:20 IST
Central Line services between Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj Terminus (CSMT) and Kalyan are running 15–20 minutes late due to waterlogged tracks.
Impact Shorts
Your shortcut to the biggest news stories
Follow us on Google News
ADVERTISEMENT
Ad
Vehicles move on a flooded road after heavy monsoon rainfall, in Mumbai. (IMAGE: PTI)

Mumbai and its neighbouring districts have been hit by heavy rainfall since Sunday night, causing widespread disruption across local train services, roads and flight schedules.

The India Meteorological Department (IMD) has issued a rain alert for the city and suburbs. Citizens are advised to stay away from coastal and low-lying areas and be cautious while travelling.

RECOMMENDED STORIES
Auto Fare Fiasco To Maid Mayhem: Why This Bengaluru Woman Wants To Leave Mumbai
IMD Warns Of Heavy Rain In Mumbai, Issues Yellow Alert For Himachal Pradesh, Jharkhand
Opinion | The Tragic Mumbai Suburban Rail Accident Was Waiting to Happen
Maharashtra reports 89 new COVID-19 cases, one casualty
Train Travel: Expect Delays

Central Line (CSMT–Kalyan): Trains are running 15–20 minutes late due to possible waterlogging on tracks.
Western Line (Virar–Churchgate): Fast locals are 5 minutes late, while slow locals are 10 minutes behind schedule.
Harbour Line (Panvel–CSMT and vice versa): Services are facing delays of 5–10 minutes.

Commuters are strongly advised to check the updated train schedules before stepping out, especially as the workweek begins. Slower train speeds have been implemented as a safety measure to avoid derailments or accidents.

Road Travel Update

Rainfall continues across Mumbai, Thane, and Navi Mumbai. While no major traffic jams have been reported, vehicle movement remains slow due to waterlogged streets and reduced visibility.

The India Meteorological Department (IMD) has issued a heavy rain alert for Mumbai and its suburbs. Authorities are requesting citizens to avoid travelling through low-lying and coastal areas.

ADVETISEMENT

For emergencies, Mumbaikars can reach help by dialling 100 / 112 / 103.

The Mumbai Police issued an alert on X (formerly Twitter) asking people to avoid coastal and flood-prone zones.

“In view of the heavy rain alert issued by IMD across Mumbai city and suburbs, citizens are requested to avoid visiting coastal and low-lying areas."

“Our officials and staff are alert and ready to assist Mumbaikars. Dial 100 / 112 / 103 in case of any emergency."

Flight Disruptions

IndiGo Airlines has also issued a travel advisory, confirming temporary disruption in flight schedules due to the downpour.

“There’s a heavy downpour over #Mumbai at the moment, causing some temporary disruption to flight schedules.

If you’re travelling today, please be aware of potential delays and allow additional time for your journey, especially with traffic moving slower than usual."

TOP VIDEOS

The heavy rain has also affected air travel, leading to temporary disruptions in flight schedules.
Passengers are requested to check their flight status before heading to the airport via the airline’s website or app.
With traffic moving slower than usual, travellers are advised to leave well in advance and allow extra time for their journey.
